<p>i'm trying to display attached videos of a post as featured-img. </p>  <p>This works great on every parent page with this code: </p>  <pre><code> &lt;?php               $attachments = get_posts(array(                'post_type' =&gt; 'attachment',                         'numberposts' =&gt; -1,                         'orderby' =&gt; 'menu_order',                         "order" =&gt; "ASC"                  ));                  if ($attachments) :                         $i = 0;                         foreach ($attachments as $attachment) :                             $attachment = get_post($attachment-&gt;ID);                             $i++;                             if ($i &gt; 1)                                 break;                             if ($attachment-&gt;post_mime_type != "video/mp4")                                 continue;                             else {                                 ?&gt;                                 &lt;video autoplay loop onclick="location.href='&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?&gt;'" muted&gt;                                     &lt;source src="&lt;?php echo $attachment-&gt;guid; ?&gt;" type="video/mp4"&gt;                                 &lt;/video&gt;                             &lt;?php                              }                             ?&gt;                         &lt;?php                         endforeach;                     endif;                     ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Unfortunately i can't get it work on child pages. I think there seems to be a problem with the post_parent attribute. I also tried to change get_posts to <code>$attachments = get_children</code>, but without success. </p>  <p>Any idea on how to solve this?  </p>  <p>cheers p</p>